"Q6","which of the following clotting factors would have decreased gamma carboxyglutamate residue in a patient on warfarin therapy?","a) Factor 2
b) Factor 11
c) Tissue factor
d) Factor 5","Factor 2 would have decreased gamma carboxyglutamate residue in a patient on warfarin therapy.
Activation of coagulation factors II, VII, IX, X is done by carboxylation of their glutamate residues. This is done by the enzyme γ-glutamyl carboxylase with the reduced form of vitamin K as a co-factor.
