b) wernicke's area
c) Auditory area
d) visual area","Broca's motor speech area is likely to be affected in the vascular injury of the inferior frontal gyrus. A lesion in this region leads to motor/Broca's aphasia. speech is non-fluent and interrupted by many word-finding pauses. The speech is impoverished in function words that contribute to the syntax but is enriched in meaningful nouns and verbs. However, comprehension of speech is intact and the patient knows what he wants to say.
